sentences: Chai along with ex-Alley Cats  John McCarthy and Randy Stodola formed The Zarkons in 1985 for which Chai sang and played bass.

Chris Morris (former senior writer at Billboard, music editor at The Hollywood Reporter and critic at The Los Angeles Reader), writing in John Doe's book Under the Big Black Sun: A Personal History of L.A. Punk, said "they made some of the toughest, most nihilistic music on the scene."
